INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '62a0404f-1c03-4016-a287-f40e027a2316',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$tailwindcss Dark Mode — CSS Custom Properties, prefers-color-scheme, and Killing the Flash$escape$,
  $escape$Tailwind's `darkMode: 'class'` strategy gives you manual control, but the real power comes from pairing it with CSS custom properties defined via Tailwind v4's `@theme` directive. Define semantic tokens — `--color-background`, `--color-surface`, `--color-foreground` — in `@theme`, then override them inside a `.dark {}` block in your global CSS. Tailwind generates utility classes (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`) directly from those tokens, keeping JSX free of raw hex values and conditional class juggling.

The flash-on-load problem hits when JS hydrates after the browser's first paint. Fix it with a blocking inline `<script>` in `<head>` — before any framework JS loads — that reads `localStorage.getItem('theme')` and falls back to `window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches`. Synchronously add `.dark` to `<html>` before the first frame renders.

Never use `useEffect` to set the initial theme; by the time it fires, the page has already painted. In Next.js App Router, place the inline script in `app/layout.tsx` via `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` with `suppressHydrationWarning` on `<html>` to silence the React hydration mismatch warning.$escape$,
  $escape$// app/layout.tsx — executes before React hydration, eliminates flash
const themeScript = `
  (function() {
    const stored = localStorage.getItem('theme');
    const prefersDark = window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches;
    if (stored === 'dark' || (!stored && prefersDark)) {
      document.documentElement.classList.add('dark');
    }
  })();
`;

export default function RootLayout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return (
    <html lang="en" suppressHydrationWarning>
      <head>
        <script dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: themeScript }} />
      </head>
      <body className="bg-background text-foreground transition-colors">{children}</body>
    </html>
  );
}$escape$,
  $escape$typescript$escape$,
