INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'e721ad8d-ef96-40c9-a397-1f5f8659d653',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Tailwind CSS Layout Primitives — Flexbox vs Grid, and When to Use Each$escape$,
  $escape$Tailwind exposes Flexbox via `flex` and Grid via `grid` — but picking the wrong one creates unnecessary complexity. Use `flex` when content drives size: navbars (`flex items-center justify-between`), button groups (`flex gap-2`), or any single-axis alignment. The children dictate the layout. Use `grid` when the layout drives content: dashboards (`grid grid-cols-12`), card galleries (`grid grid-cols-[repeat(auto-fill,minmax(280px,1fr)]`), or any design requiring strict two-axis control. Key distinction: `flex` is content-out, `grid` is layout-in. Avoid `flex flex-wrap` when you actually need `grid` — wrapping flex rows can't align across row boundaries, so columns won't line up. For the holy-grail layout (header/sidebar/main/footer), reach for `grid grid-rows-[auto_1fr_auto]` with `grid-cols-[240px_1fr]` rather than nested flex containers. Combine both: use `grid` for the page skeleton, `flex` inside each cell for component-level alignment. Tailwind's arbitrary value syntax (`grid-cols-[200px_1fr_1fr]`) covers the gaps without dropping into raw CSS.$escape$,
  $escape$// Holy-grail layout: Grid skeleton + Flex internals
<div className="grid grid-rows-[auto_1fr_auto] grid-cols-[240px_1fr] min-h-screen">
  <header className="col-span-2 flex items-center justify-between px-6 h-16 border-b">
    <span className="font-semibold">ByteAI</span>
    <nav className="flex gap-4 text-sm">
      <a href="#">Feed</a>
      <a href="#">Explore</a>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <aside className="border-r p-4 flex flex-col gap-2">
    <p className="text-xs text-muted-foreground uppercase tracking-wide">Topics</p>
  </aside>

  <main className="p-6 overflow-y-auto grid grid-cols-[repeat(auto-fill,minmax(280px,1fr))] gap-4 content-start">
    {/* card grid — layout drives content */}
  </main>

  <footer className="col-span-2 flex items-center justify-center h-12 border-t text-xs text-muted-foreground">
    © 2026 ByteAI
  </footer>
</div>$escape$,
  $escape$typescript$escape$,
