INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '156a9dd8-b787-4a4e-bfe3-da231d493481',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Tailwind CSS Performance — Critical CSS, Layout Thrash, and When will-change Backfires$escape$,
  $escape$Tailwind's JIT emits only classes present in your content glob — critical CSS is lean by default, but a greedy glob like `'./src/**/*'` can pull in bloated variant combinations. Scope it to actual template extensions.

Layout thrash hits when you animate position using `top-*`/`left-*` utilities — the browser runs layout → paint → composite on every frame. Replace them with `translate-x-*`/`translate-y-*`: these bypass layout and paint entirely, running on the compositor thread. The same trap applies to `transition-all` — it schedules recalculation for every animatable property. Use `transition-transform` or `transition-[opacity,transform]` instead.

`will-change-transform` promotes an element to its own GPU layer — correct for a single drawer or modal. Apply it across a card list and you're allocating a compositor layer per card, spiking memory with no frame-time gain. Scope it to `hover:will-change-transform` so the layer only exists during interaction, then tear it down with `will-change-auto` once the animation ends. Tailwind's `contain-layout` and `contain-paint` utilities let you wall off heavy subtrees so mutations inside don't cascade into a full-page layout recalc.$escape$,
  $escape$// ❌ Animates via layout thread — triggers layout + paint every frame
<div className="absolute top-4 left-4 transition-all duration-300" />

// ✅ Compositor-only — no layout or paint cost
<div className="translate-x-0 hover:translate-x-2 transition-transform duration-300 motion-reduce:transition-none" />

// ❌ Allocates a GPU layer per card — memory spike
{cards.map(c => <div key={c.id} className="will-change-transform rounded-xl p-4" />)}

// ✅ Layer promoted only on hover; subtree isolated from parent layout
{cards.map(c => (
  <div
    key={c.id}
    className="rounded-xl p-4 transition-transform duration-200
               hover:will-change-transform hover:-translate-y-1
               contain-layout contain-paint"
  />
))}$escape$,
