INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '7f101fd1-6a01-4c3f-bf77-a21fd56f6eb0',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$tailwindcss Dev Tooling — Wiring Prettier, Stylelint, and PostCSS for v4$escape$,
  $escape$Tailwind v4's PostCSS plugin ships as `@tailwindcss/postcss`, replacing the old dual `tailwindcss` + `autoprefixer` setup. Your `postcss.config.mjs` drops to a single plugin entry — but linting and formatting still need explicit wiring.

For class ordering, `prettier-plugin-tailwindcss` (official) sorts utilities by Tailwind's internal layer order: layout → flexbox/grid → spacing → typography → effects. In v4's CSS-first config, point it at your entrypoint via `tailwindStylesheet` so it resolves `@import "tailwindcss"` and any custom `@theme` tokens correctly.

Stylelint needs `stylelint-config-tailwindcss` alongside `stylelint-config-standard` to suppress false positives on `@apply`, `@layer`, and `@theme` directives. Without it, CI flags valid Tailwind syntax as unknown at-rules. In v4, add `@variant`, `@utility`, and `@source` to `ignoreAtRules` — these are new first-class directives that older configs don't know about.

Run Prettier before Stylelint in your lint-staged pipeline; class reordering can shift `@apply` argument order, which Stylelint then re-validates.$escape$,
  $escape$// postcss.config.mjs
export default {
  plugins: { "@tailwindcss/postcss": {} },
};

// prettier.config.mjs
export default {
  plugins: ["prettier-plugin-tailwindcss"],
  tailwindStylesheet: "./src/app/globals.css",
};

// .stylelintrc.json
{
  "extends": ["stylelint-config-standard", "stylelint-config-tailwindcss"],
  "rules": {
    "at-rule-no-unknown": [true, {
      "ignoreAtRules": ["theme", "variant", "utility", "source"]
    }]
  }
}$escape$,
  $escape$javascript$escape$,
